## Session goals

This workshop explained how to evaluate classification models beyond accuracy and document tradeoffs between false positives and false negatives.

## Key takeaways

- Always compare against a simple baseline.
- Precision/recall tradeoffs must be matched to the use case.
- Cross-validation gives more reliable estimates than a single split.

## Follow-up

Extend the notebook by plotting a precision-recall curve and discussing threshold selection.
